The latest stable version is **MSTest 4.2.2** (a major version jump from 3.8.0). Here's what affects **your code specifically**:

## Breaking change in your project

**`[ExpectedException]` was removed in v4.** Your two test methods use it. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (v4)
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## Other v4 breaking changes (don't affect your code, but good to know)

| Change | Impact |
|--------|--------|
| `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` | Only if you subclass `TestMethodAttribute` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Only if you used `ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass` |
| `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` | `.Contains()` → `.ContainsKey()` |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` instead |
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| Assert `message` + `params object[]` → just `message` | Use string interpolation |
| Dropped .NET < 8 support | You're on net8.0, so fine |

## New features you gain

- **`Assert.That()`** — expression-based assertions with auto-generated failure details
- **`CallerArgumentExpression`** — all assertions now show the expression used, not just values

Would you like me to apply the fix to your project (upgrade the package + update the test code)?
